#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Projects must always have an extended markdown description in _projects/<id>.md
# they are _not_ listed in the _data folder, only in the _projects collection folder
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Projects are ordered on the Projects page as follows:
#   by the "order" field in the projects front matter
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# the name of the project file is its unique identifier for tagging (without the ".md")
# e.g. file '/_projects/project1.md' is tagged as
# badges: 
#   - project=project1
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Jekyll frontmatter for each project is as follows:
# ---
# title: Project title
# subtitle: A bit more explanation # shown in the top banner
# description: A little bit longer description of the project, but not too long # shown in a card
# card_image: "/assets/images/restricted/portal_blur_200px.png" # optional image to illustrate the card
# order: 2
# active: true
# card_title: null # used if card_image is null; defaults to title
# categories: # allow Projects to be related to each other and viewed together via search badges on the Projects page
#     - DNA Repair
#     - Bioinformatics
# ---
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
